###  Research & Theory
* **[Communications of the ACM](https://cacm.acm.org/blogs/blog-cacm/)** - The premier publication for theoretical and applied computer science.
* **[The Morning Paper](https://blog.acolyer.org/)** - A fantastic resource that breaks down complex CS research papers into digestible summaries.
* **[Google Research Blog](https://research.google/blog/)** - Updates on the latest breakthroughs in AI, Vision, and Quantum computing.

###  Engineering & Infrastructure
* **[Netflix Tech Blog](https://netflixtechblog.com/)** - Deep dives into how Netflix handles massive traffic and chaos engineering.
* **[Cloudflare Blog](https://blog.cloudflare.com/)** - Excellent technical posts about networking, security, and the low-level mechanics of the internet.
* **[Uber Engineering](https://www.uber.com/en-US/blog/engineering/)** - Covers marketplace dynamics, data science, and mobile engineering at scale.

###  Tutorials & System Design
* **[Julia Evans (jvns.ca)](https://jvns.ca/)** - Focuses on making "scary" systems topics like DNS, Linux, and SQL accessible through visual guides.
* **[ByteByteGo](https://blog.bytebytego.com/)** - The go-to source for learning how to design large-scale distributed systems.
* **[GeeksforGeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/)** - A comprehensive portal for Data Structures, Algorithms, and core CS fundamentals.
* **[OpenAI](https://openai.com/news/)** - Essential reading for staying up-to-date with the evolution of Large Language Models.
